Direct Known Subclasses:
GraphAnalyseToolBar, TriAnalyseToolBar
public abstract class AnalyseToolBar
extends javax.swing.JToolBar

This ToolBar is placed in the south of the main frame, it is only shown when the game was started. It provides four buttons to analyse the game, it is possible to show some solutions, a base of the kernel elements or a solution together with the base of the kernel elements. At last, there can be calculated some facts about the kernel dimension and the solvability of the game.

Author:
Irene Thesing

initActions

protected void initActions()
Inits the action performed by click on the buttons. The button solve checks whether there is a solution. If there are solutions, it shows some in a new window. The button kernel shows the basic kernel elements.

initOptionPanel

public abstract MSPOption initOptionPanel(int type)
The subclasses must instantiate the option panel which shall be shown at the east border. There the displayed solutions or kernel elements should be analysed. This can be different with different games. For example in Trisentis game it is interesting to apply it on a game with additional border fields.

Parameters:
type - describes whether solutions, kernel elements or both are displayed.
Returns:
the corresponding option panel.
